node.text: Today we’re hanging out with @grossypelosi in his Brooklyn kitchen, making a dessert he ate all summer as a child: his Grandma’s Italian cream-filled sponge cake! Plus, as a treat, he’s showing three different ways you can decorate the top (a big dollop of whipped cream is required for all!). Grab the full recipe at the link in bio. #f52community

node.title: Grandma’s Italian Sponge Cake with Dan Pelosi - At Home With Us

node.text: It's summer, so we're still making all of the juicy tomato recipes like this Tomato Choka from @lesenston! The dish reflects the East Indian influence on Trinidadian cuisine but with Caribbean flair. In addition to the classic choka ingredients, a few Trinidadian staples are added to the dish, such as ginger, thyme, and shado beni. Grab the recipe at the link in bio. 📸: @juliagartland

node.text: We're back in @amandahesser's kitchen, and today, she's making fall-off-the-bone ribs that are sure to score serious points at your next barbeque. They get slathered in a rub mixture of sea salt, paprika, ground coffee beans, and peppercorns, then slow-cooked for 7 hours (for maximum flavor!). Grab Resident @ladyandpups's recipe for Coffee-Crusted Barbecue Beef Ribs at the link in bio. #f52community
